<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="756" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[491,1558,1268,2045]" box="[531,1489,1505,1530]" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[531,640,1506,1530]" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">Diagnosis</emphasis>
— Large in size (mL of Cx-I + gnathosoma ˃ 340, L genital plate ˃ 210, P-4
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[491,1558,1268,2045]" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">
˃ 170 μm); Cx-I+II apodemes protruding in both sexes, in females mediocaudal margins of Cx-IV with well-developed apodemes; anterior margin of male genital field with a bluntly pointed medial projection; L of IV-L-6 proximoventral seta 
<specimenCount box="[1137,1157,1609,1632]" pageId="4" pageNumber="756" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
˂ 20, 
<specimenCount box="[1221,1241,1609,1632]" pageId="4" pageNumber="756" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
˂ 35 μm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="760" pageId="4" pageNumber="756" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[491,1558,1268,2045]" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[531,662,1643,1667]" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">Description</emphasis>
— General feature – Colour yellowish to brown. Integument finely striated. Posteromedial margin of Cx-I rounded, caudal apodemes of Cx-I+II well-developed (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[119,186,2040,2061]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,228,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-2@5.[156,1443,220,1985]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3 Hygrobates lacrima sp. nov., holotype ♀, Mateševo, Montenegro: A – idiosoma, ventral view; B – palp, lateral view; C – palp, medial view; D – chelicera; E – I-L-5 and -6; F – IV-L-5 and -6. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5398619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5398619/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">Figs. 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[535,571,1712,1736]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[119,186,2001,2022]" captionTargetBox="[250,1348,221,1946]" captionTargetId="figure-2@6.[250,1348,221,1946]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4 Hygrobates lacrima sp. nov., ♂. Montenegro, Trebaljevo: A – idiosoma, ventral view; B – palp, medial view; C – IV-L-5 and -6. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5398621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5398621/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">4A</figureCitation>
); Cx-IV subtriangular, with a distinct nose-like protruding medial margin. Genital field (in female 
<typeStatus box="[670,766,1746,1770]" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">holotype</typeStatus>
slightly damaged during dissection and mounting): Ac in triangular arrangement (
<figureCitation box="[645,726,1781,1805]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[119,186,1946,1967]" captionTargetBox="[236,1362,231,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-2@7.[231,1366,221,1891]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5 Genital field: A-B –Hygrobates lacrima sp. nov., paratypes (A, ♂; B, ♀), Trebaljevo, Montenegro; C-F –Hygrobates limnocrenicus sp. nov. (C-D, F, ♀; E, ♂); C, holotype, Mareza, Montenegro; D, paratype, Struga, North Macedonia; E-F, Vitoja, Montenegro; G-HH –. setosus Besseling, 1942, ♂, G, Farver Au, Germany; H, redrawn from Besseling (1964)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5398623" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5398623/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
A-B). P-2 ventral margin straight, distally forming a right angle, denticles covering distal half of ventral margin; P-3 with denticles covering distal two thirds of ventral margin; P-4 ventral setae on the same level (
<figureCitation box="[973,1052,1849,1873]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[119,186,2040,2061]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,228,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-2@5.[156,1443,220,1985]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3 Hygrobates lacrima sp. nov., holotype ♀, Mateševo, Montenegro: A – idiosoma, ventral view; B – palp, lateral view; C – palp, medial view; D – chelicera; E – I-L-5 and -6; F – IV-L-5 and -6. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5398619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5398619/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
B-C, 4B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[491,1558,1268,2045]" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">
Male – Anterior margin of genital field convex, with a small bluntly pointed medial projection, posterior margin indented, with a small central protrusion not extending beyond posterior genital plate margin (
<figureCitation box="[832,925,1953,1977]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[119,186,1946,1967]" captionTargetBox="[236,1362,231,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-2@7.[231,1366,221,1891]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5 Genital field: A-B –Hygrobates lacrima sp. nov., paratypes (A, ♂; B, ♀), Trebaljevo, Montenegro; C-F –Hygrobates limnocrenicus sp. nov. (C-D, F, ♀; E, ♂); C, holotype, Mareza, Montenegro; D, paratype, Struga, North Macedonia; E-F, Vitoja, Montenegro; G-HH –. setosus Besseling, 1942, ♂, G, Farver Au, Germany; H, redrawn from Besseling (1964)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5398623" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5398623/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[491,1558,1268,2045]" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">
Female – Genital plates distinctly longer than gonopore (
<figureCitation box="[1167,1261,1987,2011]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[119,186,1946,1967]" captionTargetBox="[236,1362,231,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-2@7.[231,1366,221,1891]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5 Genital field: A-B –Hygrobates lacrima sp. nov., paratypes (A, ♂; B, ♀), Trebaljevo, Montenegro; C-F –Hygrobates limnocrenicus sp. nov. (C-D, F, ♀; E, ♂); C, holotype, Mareza, Montenegro; D, paratype, Struga, North Macedonia; E-F, Vitoja, Montenegro; G-HH –. setosus Besseling, 1942, ♂, G, Farver Au, Germany; H, redrawn from Besseling (1964)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5398623" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5398623/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="756">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
); P-4 slenderer than in male, L/H ratio 4.2-4.5.
</paragraph>
